@startuml OfflineDownloadManager_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Offline Download Manager for Social Media App (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User saves a reel for offline. Manager queues it, picks download strategy, downloads, retries on failure, notifies user."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class DownloadManager <<Singleton>> {
    - {static} instance : DownloadManager
    - downloadQueue : DownloadQueue
    - executor : DownloadExecutor
    - storageManager : StorageManager
    - networkMonitor : NetworkMonitor
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - retryPolicy : RetryPolicy
    --
    + {static} getInstance() : DownloadManager
    + download(request) : DownloadTask
    + pauseTask(taskId) : void
    + resumeTask(taskId) : void
    + cancelTask(taskId) : void
    + pauseAll() : void
    + resumeAll() : void
    + getActiveDownloads() : List<DownloadTask>
    + getDownloadHistory() : List<DownloadTask>
    + setMaxConcurrent(count) : void
}

note top of DownloadManager #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "User long-presses a reel and taps
    'Save Offline'. Client calls
    DownloadManager.download(request).
    **Singleton** — one manager per app.
    Coordinates queue, executor, storage,
    network monitoring, and retry."
    **Patterns: Facade + Singleton | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CONTENT MODEL — What are we downloading?
' ====================================================================
class DownloadRequest {
    - contentId : String
    - contentType : ContentType
    - url : String
    - quality : QualityPreference
    - userId : String
    - requestedAt : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getEstimatedSize() : long
    + getContentType() : ContentType
}

class MediaContent {
    - contentId : String
    - type : ContentType
    - title : String
    - thumbnailUrl : String
    - author : String
    - durationSeconds : int
    - availableQualities : List<QualityPreference>
    --
    + getBestQuality(networkType) : QualityPreference
}

enum ContentType {
    REEL
    VIDEO
    IMAGE
    STORY
    CAROUSEL
    AUDIO
}

enum QualityPreference {
    LOW_360P
    MEDIUM_480P
    HIGH_720P
    FULL_HD_1080P
    ORIGINAL
    AUTO
}

note top of DownloadRequest #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - What's being downloaded?**
    "**DownloadRequest**: what content, what URL,
    what quality, who requested it.
    **MediaContent**: metadata — type (REEL/VIDEO/
    IMAGE/STORY), title, duration, available
    qualities. **AUTO** quality adapts to
    current network."
end note

DownloadRequest --> ContentType
DownloadRequest --> QualityPreference
MediaContent --> ContentType
MediaContent --> QualityPreference


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: DOWNLOAD TASK + STATE PATTERN
' ====================================================================
class DownloadTask {
    - taskId : String
    - request : DownloadRequest
    - content : MediaContent
    - currentState : TaskState
    - status : TaskStatus
    - progress : DownloadProgress
    - priority : DownloadPriority
    - filePath : String
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - completedAt : LocalDateTime
    - retryCount : int
    - observers : List<DownloadObserver>
    --
    + start() : void
    + pause() : void
    + resume() : void
    + cancel() : void
    + fail(error) : void
    + complete(filePath) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
    + getProgress() : DownloadProgress
}

class DownloadProgress {
    - totalBytes : long
    - downloadedBytes : long
    - speedBytesPerSec : long
    - startedAt : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getPercent() : double
    + getEstimatedTimeRemaining() : long
    + getFormattedSpeed() : String
    + isComplete() : boolean
}

enum TaskStatus {
    QUEUED
    DOWNLOADING
    PAUSED
    COMPLETED
    FAILED
    CANCELLED
}

enum DownloadPriority {
    LOW
    NORMAL
    HIGH
    USER_INITIATED
}

note top of DownloadTask #FFCDD2
    **STEP 3 - DownloadTask is the central object.**
    "Each download becomes a DownloadTask with
    state, progress (bytes/speed/ETA), priority,
    and retry count. Uses **State Pattern**
    (lifecycle) and **Observer Pattern**
    (progress updates to UI)."
end note

DownloadTask --> DownloadRequest : for >
DownloadTask --> MediaContent : downloads >
DownloadTask --> TaskStatus
DownloadTask --> DownloadPriority
DownloadTask *-- DownloadProgress : tracks >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: STATE PATTERN — Task Lifecycle
' ====================================================================
interface TaskState <<State>> {
    + start(task) : void
    + pause(task) : void
    + resume(task) : void
    + cancel(task) : void
    + fail(task, error) : void
    + complete(task, path) : void
}

class QueuedState {
    + start(task) : void
    + cancel(task) : void
}

class DownloadingState {
    + pause(task) : void
    + cancel(task) : void
    + fail(task, error) : void
    + complete(task, path) : void
}

class PausedState {
    + resume(task) : void
    + cancel(task) : void
}

class CompletedState {
    ' terminal — file saved
}

class FailedState {
    + resume(task) : void
    + cancel(task) : void
}

class CancelledState {
    ' terminal — cleanup done
}

note bottom of TaskState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Task lifecycle.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    **Queued**: waiting in queue, can start/cancel.
    **Downloading**: active, can pause/fail/complete.
    **Paused**: user paused or network lost, can resume.
    **Failed**: error occurred, can retry (resume).
    **Completed/Cancelled**: terminal."

    Queued -> Downloading -> Completed
    Downloading -> Paused -> Downloading
    Downloading -> Failed -> Downloading (retry)
    Any -> Cancelled
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

TaskState <|.. QueuedState
TaskState <|.. DownloadingState
TaskState <|.. PausedState
TaskState <|.. CompletedState
TaskState <|.. FailedState
TaskState <|.. CancelledState
DownloadTask --> TaskState : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: DOWNLOAD QUEUE — Priority Queue
' ====================================================================
class DownloadQueue {
    - queue : PriorityQueue<DownloadTask>
    - maxConcurrent : int
    - activeCount : int
    --
    + enqueue(task) : void
    + dequeueNext() : DownloadTask
    + peek() : DownloadTask
    + remove(taskId) : void
    + reprioritize(taskId, priority) : void
    + getQueueSize() : int
    + getActiveCount() : int
}

note bottom of DownloadQueue #C8E6C9
    **STEP 5 - Queue with priorities.**
    "Downloads don't all start at once.
    PriorityQueue orders by DownloadPriority.
    USER_INITIATED > HIGH > NORMAL > LOW.
    maxConcurrent limits parallel downloads
    (e.g., 3 at a time). When one finishes,
    next in queue starts automatically."
end note

DownloadManager --> DownloadQueue : manages >
DownloadQueue o--> DownloadTask : queues >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: DOWNLOAD STRATEGY — Strategy Pattern (CORE)
' ====================================================================
interface DownloadStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + download(url, destPath, progressCallback) : void
    + supportsResume() : boolean
    + getChunkSize() : int
}

class SimpleDownloadStrategy {
    --
    + download(url, destPath, progressCallback) : void
    + supportsResume() : boolean
}

class ChunkedDownloadStrategy {
    - chunkSizeBytes : int
    - parallelChunks : int
    --
    + download(url, destPath, progressCallback) : void
    + supportsResume() : boolean
}

class StreamingDownloadStrategy {
    - bufferSizeBytes : int
    --
    + download(url, destPath, progressCallback) : void
    + supportsResume() : boolean
}

class DownloadExecutor {
    - strategySelector : DownloadStrategySelector
    - activeDownloads : Map<String, Thread>
    --
    + execute(task) : void
    + cancelExecution(taskId) : void
    + isExecuting(taskId) : boolean
}

class DownloadStrategySelector {
    --
    + selectStrategy(content, network) : DownloadStrategy
}

note bottom of DownloadStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 6 - How to actually download? (KEY STEP)**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — download mechanism
    is pluggable."

    "**SimpleDownload**: single HTTP GET, for images.
    **ChunkedDownload**: splits into parallel chunks
    with resume support — for large videos.
    **StreamingDownload**: progressive, low-memory
    — for reels/stories."

    "**StrategySelector** auto-picks based on
    content type + network: WiFi -> Chunked
    parallel, Mobile -> Simple sequential."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

DownloadStrategy <|.. SimpleDownloadStrategy
DownloadStrategy <|.. ChunkedDownloadStrategy
DownloadStrategy <|.. StreamingDownloadStrategy
DownloadExecutor --> DownloadStrategySelector : uses >
DownloadStrategySelector --> DownloadStrategy : selects >
DownloadManager --> DownloadExecutor : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: NETWORK MONITOR — Observer Pattern
' ====================================================================
class NetworkMonitor {
    - currentType : NetworkType
    - isConnected : boolean
    - observers : List<NetworkObserver>
    --
    + getCurrentType() : NetworkType
    + isConnected() : boolean
    + isOnWifi() : boolean
    + getEstimatedBandwidth() : long
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    - onNetworkChanged(newType) : void
}

interface NetworkObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onNetworkChange(oldType, newType, connected) : void
}

class AutoPauseHandler <<ConcreteObserver>> {
    - wifiOnlyMode : boolean
    --
    + onNetworkChange(oldType, newType, connected) : void
}

class QualityAdaptHandler <<ConcreteObserver>> {
    --
    + onNetworkChange(oldType, newType, connected) : void
}

enum NetworkType {
    WIFI
    MOBILE_4G
    MOBILE_5G
    MOBILE_3G
    OFFLINE
}

note bottom of NetworkObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - React to network changes.**
    "Social media app — user moves from WiFi
    to mobile data. **Observer Pattern**."

    "**AutoPauseHandler**: if wifiOnlyMode=true,
    pause all downloads when WiFi lost.
    Resume when WiFi returns.
    **QualityAdaptHandler**: downgrade quality
    from 1080p to 480p on slow network."

    "Network lost entirely? Pause all.
    Reconnected? Resume automatically."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

NetworkObserver <|.. AutoPauseHandler
NetworkObserver <|.. QualityAdaptHandler
NetworkMonitor --> NetworkObserver : notifies >
NetworkMonitor --> NetworkType
DownloadManager --> NetworkMonitor : monitors >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: STORAGE MANAGER
' ====================================================================
class StorageManager {
    - basePath : String
    - maxStorageBytes : long
    - evictionPolicy : EvictionPolicy
    --
    + getAvailableSpace() : long
    + hasSpace(requiredBytes) : boolean
    + saveToDisk(taskId, data, path) : String
    + deleteFile(path) : void
    + getOfflineContent() : List<MediaContent>
    + getTotalUsed() : long
    + evictIfNeeded(requiredBytes) : void
}

interface EvictionPolicy <<Strategy>> {
    + selectForEviction(contents, bytesNeeded) : List<MediaContent>
}

class LRUEvictionPolicy {
    --
    + selectForEviction(contents, bytesNeeded) : List<MediaContent>
}

class SizeBasedEvictionPolicy {
    --
    + selectForEviction(contents, bytesNeeded) : List<MediaContent>
}

class OldestFirstEvictionPolicy {
    --
    + selectForEviction(contents, bytesNeeded) : List<MediaContent>
}

note bottom of EvictionPolicy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 8 - Where does it go? Storage is finite.**
    "Phone storage is limited. StorageManager
    checks hasSpace() before downloading.
    If full, **EvictionPolicy** decides what to remove."

    "**Strategy Pattern** — eviction is pluggable.
    **LRU**: remove least recently viewed.
    **SizeBased**: remove largest files first.
    **OldestFirst**: remove oldest downloads."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

EvictionPolicy <|.. LRUEvictionPolicy
EvictionPolicy <|.. SizeBasedEvictionPolicy
EvictionPolicy <|.. OldestFirstEvictionPolicy
StorageManager --> EvictionPolicy : delegates >
DownloadManager --> StorageManager : stores via >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: RETRY POLICY
' ====================================================================
interface RetryPolicy <<Strategy>> {
    + shouldRetry(task, error, attemptCount) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attemptCount) : long
}

class ExponentialBackoffRetry {
    - maxRetries : int
    - baseDelayMs : long
    --
    + shouldRetry(task, error, attemptCount) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attemptCount) : long
}

class FixedIntervalRetry {
    - maxRetries : int
    - intervalMs : long
    --
    + shouldRetry(task, error, attemptCount) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attemptCount) : long
}

class NoRetry {
    + shouldRetry(task, error, attemptCount) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attemptCount) : long
}

note bottom of RetryPolicy #FFCDD2
    **STEP 9 - Handle failures gracefully.**
    "Network drops mid-download. What now?"

    "**Strategy Pattern** — retry logic is pluggable.
    **ExponentialBackoff**: 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s (avoids
    server hammering). **FixedInterval**: every 5s.
    **NoRetry**: fail immediately (user-cancelled)."

    "ChunkedDownload supports resume from
    last byte — no re-downloading."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

RetryPolicy <|.. ExponentialBackoffRetry
RetryPolicy <|.. FixedIntervalRetry
RetryPolicy <|.. NoRetry
DownloadManager --> RetryPolicy : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 10: DOWNLOAD OBSERVER — Progress + Notifications
' ====================================================================
interface DownloadObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onProgressUpdate(task) : void
    + onStateChange(task, oldState, newState) : void
}

class UIProgressObserver {
    --
    + onProgressUpdate(task) : void
    + onStateChange(task, oldState, newState) : void
}

class NotificationBarObserver {
    --
    + onProgressUpdate(task) : void
    + onStateChange(task, oldState, newState) : void
}

class AnalyticsObserver {
    --
    + onProgressUpdate(task) : void
    + onStateChange(task, oldState, newState) : void
}

class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notifyComplete(task) : void
    + notifyFailed(task) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

class SystemNotification {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

class InAppToast {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

note bottom of DownloadObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 10 - Keep the user informed.**
    "**Observer Pattern** — on progress/state change:"

    "**UIProgressObserver**: updates the progress
    bar in the downloads screen (% + speed).
    **NotificationBarObserver**: shows system
    notification with progress.
    **AnalyticsObserver**: logs download metrics
    (speed, success rate, content type)."

    "Notification channel via **Strategy**:
    SystemNotification vs InAppToast."
    **Patterns: Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

DownloadObserver <|.. UIProgressObserver
DownloadObserver <|.. NotificationBarObserver
DownloadObserver <|.. AnalyticsObserver
DownloadTask --> DownloadObserver : notifies >
NotificationStrategy <|.. SystemNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. InAppToast
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy
DownloadManager --> NotificationService


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "User saves a reel -> DownloadManager queues it with
    priority -> Queue pops it when slot opens -> StrategySelector picks
    ChunkedDownload for video on WiFi -> Download progresses, observer
    updates UI -> Network drops? AutoPauseHandler pauses, resumes on
    reconnect -> Failure? ExponentialBackoff retries -> Storage full?
    LRU eviction frees space -> Complete: file saved, user notified.
    5 patterns: **Singleton/Facade**, **Strategy** (x4), **State**, **Observer** (x2)."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | User taps 'Save Offline', calls DownloadManager | Facade + Singleton | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | DownloadRequest: content type, URL, quality preference | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | DownloadTask created with state, progress, priority | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Queued -> Downloading -> Paused -> Completed / Failed | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 5 | PriorityQueue: USER_INITIATED > HIGH > NORMAL > LOW | -- | SRP |
    | 6 | Simple / Chunked / Streaming download strategy (auto-selected) | Strategy | OCP, DIP |
    | 7 | Network lost: auto-pause. WiFi back: auto-resume. Quality adapts | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Storage full: LRU / SizeBased / OldestFirst eviction | Strategy | OCP, DIP |
    | 9 | Failure: exponential backoff retry, resume from last byte | Strategy | OCP |
    | 10 | UI progress bar, notification bar, analytics all updated | Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Queue + Execute** = Steps 5-6 | **Lifecycle** = Step 4 | **Resilience** = Steps 7,9 | **Storage** = Step 8 |
endlegend

@enduml
